-- Japan Beats Denmark 3-1 to Advance at World Cup; Netherlands Wins Group
-- Bob Bensch
-- 2010-06-24T20:38:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-24/japan-beats-denmark-3-1-to-advance-at-world-cup-netherlands-wins-group.html

          
          
             Japan beat Denmark 3-1 to advance to
the round of 16 at the World Cup, while the Netherlands defeated
Cameroon 2-1 to finish atop Group E.  
 Keisuke Honda, Yasuhito Endo and Shinji Okazaki scored for
Japan in Rustenburg, South Africa.  Robin van Persie  and  Klaas Jan Huntelaar  had the Netherlands goals in Cape Town.  
 The Netherlands, which had already qualified for the second
round, finished with nine points, three more than Japan. Denmark
had three points and Cameroon zero.  
 Earlier today, Slovakia beat Italy 3-2 in Group F to move
into the next round and eliminate the defending World Cup
champion. Paraguay won the group after a 0-0 tie with New
Zealand.  
 The Netherlands will face Slovakia on June 28, with
Paraguay meeting Japan the following day.  
